      <section eId="sec_52_4_2">
        <num>52-4-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>When the petition for incorporation has been made and filed and the fee paid, as provided in Code Section 52-4-1, the Secretary of State shall issue to the petitioners a certificate as follows:</p>
          <p>"Georgia. To whom it may concern - Greetings:</p>
          <p>______ having filed their petition in the terms of the law, praying to be incorporated as a canal company, they and their associates and successors are hereby declared to be a body corporate for the period of 30 years, under the name of ______, with power to construct, maintain, and operate a canal in and through ______, with such powers, privileges, and liabilities as may now or hereafter be prescribed by law.</p>
          <p>Witness my official hand and seal of state, this ______ day of ____________, ________."</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1893, p. 81, § 1; Civil Code 1895, § 1987; Civil Code 1910, § 2368; Code 1933, § 17-102; Ga. L. 1999, p. 81, § 52.)</p>
        </content>
      </section>
